Specification&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-fonts-4/#font-variant-emoji-prop"&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/css-fonts-4/#font-variant-emoji-prop&lt;/a&gt;
Design docs &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NyIKm0PnWUwX6j0smDwxDAPSUoiyBHPL95oH2lvjjpc/edit?usp=sharing&amp;resourcekey=0-ubYsGJCgRSQnT9i_guM64g"&gt;https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NyIKm0PnWUwX6j0smDwxDAPSUoiyBHPL95oH2lvjjpc/edit?usp=sharing&amp;resourcekey=0-ubYsGJCgRSQnT9i_guM64g&lt;/a&gt;
Summary
Font-variant-emoji CSS property provides users an easy way to control between colored (emoji-style) and monochromatic (text-style) emoji glyphs presentations. This can be also done by adding an emoji Variation Selector, specifically U+FE0E for text and U+FE0F for emojis, after each emoji codepoint. Using font-variant-emoji CSS property allows web developers to select between emoji style (colored) emoji presentation, text style (monochromatic) emoji presentation and unicode default emoji presentation [0]. This property only affects emojis that are part of a Unicode emoji presentation sequence [1]. [0] &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr51/tr51-25.html#Emoji_Presentation"&gt;https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr51/tr51-25.html#Emoji_Presentation&lt;/a&gt; [1] &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.unicode.org/emoji/charts/emoji-variants.html"&gt;http://www.unicode.org/emoji/charts/emoji-variants.html&lt;/a&gt;
